Description: Fragment of neck and round handle to moderate turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Aristombrotidas. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0085.18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1160)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (probably)
